This example will plot a Tai Chi Yin Yang figure using local refinement technique
The obtained solution is saved in file "D.dx".

Usage:
	1. compile with make [-e debug=no];
	2. generate the mesh with easymesh as:
               $ easymesh D
	3. run with ./run.sh D n, here the second parameter n means times for the initial global refinement of mesh grids.
	4. view the obtained numerical solution with OpenDX;

